   <mods:abstract>With regard to the three letters John Jay had sent him: 1. Cannot comment
            on the Corsair held in the Canary Islands until he has more information. 2. With regard
            to the bills in John JayÆs name for ten to eleven thousand gros piastres held by Messrs.
            Joyce, cannot do anything until he has consulted with the king and other ministers, some
            of whom have already left for Madrid. John Jay will have to ask Messrs. Joyce for a few
            more days. 3. As for the project John Jay outlined, in which the king would underwrite a
            loan to Congress in exchange for ships, John Jay should be more specific and name the
            amount for which the king would be obliged. In French.</mods:abstract>
